23/03/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Despite a warning by the Office of the High Representative (OHR) that the candidate vetting process was not yet complete, the Federation of BiH (FBiH) House of Representatives elected the new entity government on Thursday (March 22nd). 
The ruling coalition includes the Party for Democratic Action (SDA), Party for BiH, Croatian Democratic Union BiH, and the Croatian Democratic Union 1990. 
SDA's Nedzad Brankovic, FBiH's former transport and communications minister, was elected prime minister.
In other news Thursday, BiH police detained Nisvet Gasal and Musajb Kukavica, former Bosnian Muslim wartime officials accused of crimes against Croats during the country's 1992-1995 conflict. 
This was the first such arrest related to crimes against Croats. 
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 23/03/07; RTRS, Fena, PBS, OHR website, Reuters - 22/03/07)
